\pard\nowidctlpar Excellent post and example. Essentially multiplication of two polynomials means that every term in one polynomial needs to be multiplied with every term in the other polynomial.  For example, (x-1)(x^2+x+1) = x*x^2+x*x+x*1-1*x^2-1*x-1*1 = x^3+x^2+x-x^2-x-1=x^3-1.\par
\par
Now what about multiplication of more than two polynomials? We use the same method and each time we multiply two of them. For example,\par
(x-1)(x-1)(x-1)=[(x-1)(x-1)](x-1) = [x*x+x*(-1)-1*x+(-1)*(-1)](x-1) = [x^2-2x+1](x-1) = x^2*x-x^2*1-2x*x-2x*(-1)+x-1 = x^3-3x^2+3x-1.\par

