\pard\nowidctlpar A common mistake when dealing with polynomial is to confuse two terms like 2x^3 and (2x)^3. Because the priority of exponentiation is higher than that of multiplication, we won't multiply 2 three times by itself when evaluating 2x^3, hence 2x^3 is not equal to 8x^3. On the other hand, because the priority of parentheses is higher than that of exponentiation, we do need to multiply 2 three times by it self when evaluating (2x)^3, hence (2x^3)=8x^3. \par
